PLANT VIRUS RNA IN GLACIAL ICE (02)
***************************
A ProMED post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>

[see: Plant virus RNA in glacial ice 991009102724]
Date: Mon, 11 Oct 1999 09:00:02 +1000
From: "Adrian Gibbs" <GIBBS@rsbs.anu.edu.au>

The report [ref. above] should be treated with healthy scepticism. Earlier
papers by the same authors might indicate that the source of ToMV was the
rinsing water for the plastic centrifuge tubes. Polar Biology is not well
known as a virological journal.
Adrian Gibbs
